com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.platform.controller

Class SCUIController

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.platform.controller.SCUIController
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SCUIXAPIMashupController

    public abstract class SCUIController
extends java.lang.Object
    Any controller class needs to extend this method. And it should override its onExecute method. By default, the onExecute method does nothing. Execute method of this class, first authenticates the controller based on the resourceId parameter provided for the controller definition. It then executes the onExecute method.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public final void execute(SCUIControllerObject controllerObj,
                          org.w3c.dom.Element input,
                          SCUIContext uiContext)
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        This method first does the authorization check for controller resource using #authorize(SCUIContext) method. Once the authorization is done, #onExecute(SCUIContext) method is called on the object. Any returned value by onExecute method is returned as result by this controller. This method catches SCUIAuthorizationException, SCUIValidationException and SCUIException, which can be thrown either by #authorize(SCUIContext) or #onExecute(SCUIContext) methods.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • authorize

        protected void authorize(SCUIControllerObject controllerObj,
                         org.w3c.dom.Element input,
                         SCUIContext uiContext)
        This method authorizes user against resourceId provided in action definition. If not resourceId is provided, authorization check is skipped.
        If authorization fails, a SCUIAuthorizationException is thrown; if successful a Boolean attribute SCUIConstants#STRUTS_ACTION_AUTHORIZED is set on the uiContext. uiContext
